Step-by-Step Setup
Step 1: Create IAM Roles / Users

Create required IAM roles:

CodePipeline Role
CodeBuild Role
CodeDeploy Role
EC2 Role (if deploying to EC2)

Grant permissions for:

S3
CodeCommit
CodeBuild
CodeDeploy
CloudWatch Logs
Step 2: Create KMS Key (Optional)

Use AWS Key Management Service to encrypt:

S3 artifacts bucket
Pipeline data
Secrets
Step 3: Create CodeCommit Repository

Create repo:

demo-app

Clone repo locally:

git clone <repo-url>

Push project files:

index.html
appspec.yml
buildspec.yml
Step 4: Create S3 Artifact Bucket

Create bucket:

demo-app-artifacts

Used by pipeline to store:

source zip
build outputs
deployment bundles
Step 5: Add buildspec.yml

Example:

version: 0.2

phases:
  install:
    commands:
      - echo Install phase

  build:
    commands:
      - echo Build started

artifacts:
  files:
    - '**/*'
Step 6: Create CodeBuild Project

Configure:

Source = CodeCommit
Environment = Managed Image
OS = Ubuntu
Runtime = Standard
Buildspec = use repo file
Step 7: Create Deployment Target

Choose one:

Option A: EC2

Install CodeDeploy agent on EC2.

Option B: ECS

Deploy containers.

Option C: Lambda

Deploy serverless function.

Step 8: Add appspec.yml (for EC2)
version: 0.0
os: linux

files:
  - source: /
    destination: /var/www/html
Step 9: Create CodeDeploy Application
Platform = EC2 / ECS / Lambda
Create deployment group
Step 10: Create CodePipeline

Stages:

Source Stage
CodeCommit repo
Build Stage
CodeBuild project
Deploy Stage
CodeDeploy target
Step 11: Trigger Pipeline

Push code:

git add .
git commit -m "new changes"
git push origin main

Pipeline auto starts.

Step 12: Monitor

Check:

CodePipeline stages
CodeBuild logs
CodeDeploy deployment status
CloudWatch logs
